Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Handle, gradual curve. Circular stamp. Clay near fine buff-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.102, 23).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1230)
